26:44.353 --> 26:46.060
You're not taking her anywhere.

26:50.901 --> 26:52.733
She's my niece.

26:53.403 --> 26:54.734
I don't know you.

26:57.241 --> 26:58.948
- Come on.
- Wait.

27:00.244 --> 27:01.655
You're Uncle Miles?

27:02.913 --> 27:06.872
- Underwhelmed?
- No, I just-- I mean, I didn't expect--

27:07.042 --> 27:09.409
Come on. Not in here.

27:14.383 --> 27:16.215
[GUN COCKS]

27:22.933 --> 27:26.221
- No funny business, now.
- No, ma'am, I'm--

27:28.897 --> 27:30.433
I'm not--

27:31.775 --> 27:33.891
- What happened?
- Well, if you gonna have an asthma attack...

27:36.155 --> 27:39.113
...at least you had the good sense
to have it near me.

27:39.449 --> 27:40.939
Here.

27:44.746 --> 27:47.579
- What is this?
- You breathe it in.

27:47.791 --> 27:50.909
- Stops the attack before it starts.
- You're a doctor?

27:51.086 --> 27:52.542
It was my son's.

27:55.132 --> 27:56.793
Now, you wanna explain this?

28:01.013 --> 28:03.095
I was running away from some soldiers.

28:03.307 --> 28:05.469
- Monroe's boys?
- Yes.

28:06.268 --> 28:08.760
- Did they follow you here?
- Look, look.

28:08.979 --> 28:15.601
I don't mean to put you to any more trouble,
and I owe you already, so I'll just...

28:20.574 --> 28:22.190
<i>I'll go.</i>

28:26.955 --> 28:33.076
That's it. He said to come find you
and that you'd help us and, uh...

28:33.462 --> 28:35.624
And then he...

28:36.006 --> 28:37.121
Yeah.

28:37.841 --> 28:39.377
I'm sorry.

28:40.844 --> 28:42.175
I wish I could've...

28:46.850 --> 28:48.306
Why did Monroe want my Dad?

28:49.561 --> 28:51.347
And why does he want you?

28:52.522 --> 28:56.140
Monroe thinks your dad knew something.
Something important.

28:56.360 --> 28:59.853
And he thinks your dad told me,
so I must know it too.

29:00.697 --> 29:01.983
What?

29:04.117 --> 29:05.983
Why the lights went out.

29:06.161 --> 29:08.573
Maybe how to turn them back on.

29:08.789 --> 29:11.076
If Monroe got the power going...

29:11.291 --> 29:15.706
...that would mean tanks and planes...

29:15.921 --> 29:17.332
...factories.

29:18.340 --> 29:22.925
He'd steamroll the entire continent,
and he'd butcher the other republics.

29:25.055 --> 29:26.637
Okay.

29:27.808 --> 29:29.173
So, what do we do now?

29:30.018 --> 29:32.305
"What do we do now"?
About what?

29:32.854 --> 29:34.310
How are we gonna get Danny back?

29:36.942 --> 29:38.558
I didn't say I was going with you.

29:39.361 --> 29:40.442
What?

29:40.654 --> 29:45.524
In case you haven't noticed, I'm trying
to maintain a certain low profile here.

29:47.035 --> 29:50.949
- No, look. Look, I'm begging you--
- Your brother is bait.

29:52.249 --> 29:56.538
You understand that?
I go after it, not good for him.

29:56.712 --> 29:57.873
Or for me.

29:58.088 --> 30:00.705
I, for one, would like to keep my insides
on the inside.

30:00.924 --> 30:04.167
No. No, look, I have--

30:05.304 --> 30:09.298
I have lost everyone that I care about.

30:09.558 --> 30:11.765
My mom is dead.

30:12.436 --> 30:15.474
My dad is dead.

30:15.689 --> 30:18.056
And God knows what they're doing
to Danny right now.

30:18.275 --> 30:22.940
- So you are gonna help me get him back.
- Why's that?

30:24.906 --> 30:26.442
Because we're family.

30:27.826 --> 30:29.612
Family?

30:30.954 --> 30:32.786
Kid, I don't even know you.

30:38.086 --> 30:39.793
Yeah, you're right.

30:42.591 --> 30:46.084
And it was stupid of me to ask.
Sorry to bother you.

30:51.892 --> 30:53.223
- What's wrong?
- Let's get out.

30:53.435 --> 30:54.516
Charlie, what's wrong?

30:54.728 --> 30:56.014
- Nothing. Let's go.
- Tell me.

30:56.229 --> 30:58.095
- Just get your stuff.
- Hey, what happened?

30:58.315 --> 31:00.477
Nothing. Let's just go.

31:01.276 --> 31:04.394
- Let's just go. Come on.
- Hey. Hold on.

31:06.156 --> 31:08.443
- Step back.
- So, what did you say to her, huh?

31:12.621 --> 31:14.237
MILES:
Militia, huh?

31:14.664 --> 31:16.325
When did you enlist?

31:39.981 --> 31:42.564
CHARLIE:
Uncle Miles, this is my fault. I'm so sorry.

31:43.360 --> 31:46.068
He's probably from the same unit
that took your brother.

31:46.696 --> 31:50.564
Been following you from the get-go,
hoping you'd flush me out...

31:51.368 --> 31:53.609
...which is exactly what you did, isn't it?

31:53.829 --> 31:56.241
AARON:
So, what are you gonna do?

31:57.958 --> 32:01.326
This, as far as I know...

32:02.254 --> 32:05.337
...is the last bottle of single malt in Chicago.

32:05.549 --> 32:08.007
My plan is to sit here and drink it.

32:08.218 --> 32:11.210
- You can't just stay here. It's not safe.
- Whose fault is that?

32:11.430 --> 32:14.218
Your boyfriend.
He's gonna go and get the nearest squad.

32:14.433 --> 32:17.642
Two, maybe three hours, tops,
is what you got.

32:17.853 --> 32:20.390
So if I were you guys, I'd hit the road.

32:20.605 --> 32:23.563
This is crazy. Just come with us.

32:23.775 --> 32:24.936
Or don't, that's fine.

32:25.152 --> 32:28.110
But go somewhere.
You can't just sit here and die.

32:28.864 --> 32:30.275
Just go.

32:30.740 --> 32:32.276
Uncle Miles, come on.

32:33.452 --> 32:34.613
I said go.

32:38.623 --> 32:40.489
Get out!

32:41.126 --> 32:42.958
Get out of here!

33:01.771 --> 33:03.102
Good morning, may I help you?

33:03.315 --> 33:06.353
Sorry to bother you. We're looking
for a dangerous young fugitive.

33:06.568 --> 33:09.936
Nineteen, 6 feet, brown hair.

33:11.114 --> 33:13.697
You're the first person I've seen in weeks.

33:18.246 --> 33:20.487
What did you do before the Blackout?

33:20.999 --> 33:22.535
Sorry?

33:22.751 --> 33:26.494
Just curious. Humor me, please.

33:27.714 --> 33:28.795
I taught algebra.

33:29.508 --> 33:32.170
Me, I was an insurance adjuster.

33:32.928 --> 33:34.635
[CHUCKLES]

33:35.222 --> 33:40.592
Most of my job was figuring out whether
things people said lined up with the truth.

33:40.810 --> 33:44.144
Lucky for me,
it's a skill that never goes out of style.

33:44.356 --> 33:48.441
So take, for example, those tracks
that lead right to your back door.

33:48.652 --> 33:51.110
- Tracks?
- Fresh ones.

33:51.321 --> 33:52.903
About a day old.

33:53.114 --> 33:54.320
Two people.

33:54.533 --> 33:58.117
A woman, who would have to be you,
dragging in a man...

33:58.328 --> 34:03.539
...and yet you say that I'm the first person
you've seen in weeks.

34:04.793 --> 34:08.331
So tell me,
does that sound like the truth to you?

34:47.127 --> 34:48.458
He's gotta be long gone.

34:51.089 --> 34:53.581
If he's here, Monroe wants him alive.

35:05.770 --> 35:07.010
Come on down.

35:07.230 --> 35:08.391
We don't wanna hurt you.

35:10.025 --> 35:11.982
MILES:
I don't wanna hurt them.

35:13.778 --> 35:15.769
But I'm not going back.

35:16.865 --> 35:19.527
You could just let me go.
I'll drink myself to death.

35:20.744 --> 35:22.280
You know we can't do that.

35:24.998 --> 35:26.079
I know.

35:26.416 --> 35:27.781
Take him.

35:28.126 --> 35:29.366
NOW!

35:41.806 --> 35:43.342
Shoot him.

36:38.863 --> 36:40.024
Unh!

36:42.075 --> 36:43.611
[GRUNTS]

37:02.220 --> 37:03.255
Ugh!

37:53.188 --> 37:54.724
MAGGIE:
Charlie?

37:59.861 --> 38:01.443
You okay?

38:09.871 --> 38:11.202
SOLDIER:
Argh!

38:39.526 --> 38:42.109
You know,
I didn't ask you to come back.

38:43.071 --> 38:45.403
Don't look at me, I wanted to let you rot.

38:46.032 --> 38:48.524
- Why didn't you?
- Because we're family.

38:48.743 --> 38:50.529
And that's what Dad would've wanted.

38:51.496 --> 38:52.861
Kid...

38:53.498 --> 38:56.206
...if I'm coming with you, you're gonna
have to dial it back a notch.

38:57.460 --> 38:59.121
You're coming?

38:59.462 --> 39:02.329
Loverboy will just send more troops.

39:04.676 --> 39:06.758
And I can't stay here.

39:08.847 --> 39:09.928
Thank you.

39:12.350 --> 39:13.806
You're welcome.

39:14.018 --> 39:17.352
We're all gonna end up with our heads
on a stick, but you're welcome.

39:47.260 --> 39:51.049
Bass, what the hell is going on?

39:51.556 --> 39:54.048
MONROE:
I don't know. But we should get back to base.

39:56.978 --> 39:58.468
MONROE:
This is not good.

39:58.688 --> 40:01.476
Hold it right there, gentlemen. IDs?

40:03.067 --> 40:05.308
Sergeant Miles Matheson.

40:08.323 --> 40:09.404
You're good.

40:10.074 --> 40:12.065
MONROE:
I only...

40:12.994 --> 40:14.359
Well, he knows me.

40:14.579 --> 40:16.286
Sergeant Sebastian Monroe.

40:20.543 --> 40:21.908
You're good.

40:29.302 --> 40:30.963
Miles?

41:05.463 --> 41:07.124
SOLDIER:
General Monroe.

43:16.469 --> 43:18.460
[English - US - SDH]
